---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '@lib/config';
---

<BaseLayout title="about" description={`About ${SITE.author}`}>
  <section class="container about">
    <h1># about</h1>

    <pre class="ascii" aria-hidden="true">
{`$ cat /etc/motd

   role        : infra & devops engineer
   focus       : kubernetes, observability, automation
   interests   : homelab, security, self-hosting
   pgp         : (publish a key here)
   contact     : hello@marc-os.com`}
    </pre>

    <p>
      Hi — I'm Marc. I run servers for fun and occasionally for money. This site is where
      I take notes in public about things I've learned the hard way.
    </p>

    <h2>## stack of choice</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>infra</strong>: terraform, ansible, nix on the edges</li>
      <li><strong>runtime</strong>: docker, kubernetes (k3s at home)</li>
      <li><strong>obs</strong>: prometheus + grafana + loki, alloy on hosts</li>
      <li><strong>edge</strong>: nginx proxy manager, traefik, cloudflare tunnels</li>
      <li><strong>cli</strong>: zsh, neovim, tmux, the usual suspects</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>## this site</h2>
    <p>
      Built with <a href="https://astro.build" rel="noopener">Astro</a>. Content is plain
      markdown in <code>src/content/</code>. Themed with
      <a href="https://catppuccin.com" rel="noopener">Catppuccin Mocha</a>.
      No JS frameworks, no third-party trackers, no analytics, no databases.
    </p>
    <p>
      Hosted on a single VPS, served by a hardened container fronted by
      Nginx Proxy Manager. Source is on <a href={SITE.social.github} rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { padding: 2rem 1.25rem 3rem; }
  .about h1 { margin-top: 0; }
  .ascii {
    color: var(--ctp-teal);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    background: var(--bg-deep);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  strong { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
